Quarto basics

You already have quite a bit of experience with creating basic R Quarto documents. You will want to create a more appealing document. Here are a few more tips to help you get started with this. For a comprehensive guide, see https://quarto.org/docs/guide/.

Additional Markdown formatting

You can embed additional levels of subheadings by using more hashes. To make text appear bold or in italics use asterisks. For embedded code, use backticks, e.g.Â to refer to a function such as filter().

There are many more options, e.g.Â allowing you to embed tables. See the Markdown basics section of the Quarto documentation for further details.1

Customising overall appearance

To customise the overall appearance of your Quarto document, you can change the theme. This document use the zephyr theme, with a title block banner. See the html theming section of the Quarto documentation for further details.

There are also many other options, e.g.Â in regard to including a table of contents (or not) and how it is displayed. We have been working with html output and will continue to do so. However, you can also produce other output formats like pdf (again, see the documentation for details).

If you want to share your document with others, you will usually want to set the self-contained option to true (see line 12 of the header).

Customising code chunks

You may or may not want code to appear in your output. You can customise the behaviour of individual code chunks by setting the appropriate option at the beginning of the chunk using the #| syntax. For example, the chunk below runs code to create a penguins plot but does not display the code itself in the knitted document. This is accomplished by adding echo: false as a parameter. If you want to set echo: false for all chunks, you can do this by replacing the echo: truein line 13 of the header. As you can see, the header also sets warning: false and message: false for the entire document, so that warnings and messages (e.g.Â the one that you normally see when you load the tidyverse) arenât included in the output.
